Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Development Engineer* position with *Amazon*. I bring over three years of professional experience building distributed systems, multi-channel communication backends, and production AI-powered services, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY (GPA 4.0/4.0).

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade distributed systems that directly reflect the depth of building scalable, fault-tolerant software for millions of users. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I designed a multi-tiered, distributed multi-agent CRM platform using LangGraph, LangChain, and FastAPI that routes 10,000+ user requests across 40+ specialized Object-Oriented sub-agents — with tenant-aware access control and lazy-loaded tool context keeping the system both secure and operationally lean. Alongside it, I engineered a scalable, fault-tolerant MCP server using FastMCP that exposes 160+ AI-powered tool actions over a multi-threaded, multi-tenant backend, automating multi-channel CRM workflow execution with built-in OpenTelemetry monitoring. To keep these systems continuously deployable, I built GitHub Actions CI/CD pipelines with OpenTelemetry trace-based evals that gate every release on latency, accuracy, and safety — enforcing full software development life cycle discipline from code reviews and source control management through build processes and automated testing. I also built LlamaIndex-powered RAG agents using OpenAI embeddings and Pgvector to deliver ready-to-run REST API examples, integrating AI-powered capabilities with a customer-obsessed focus on both technical and non-technical user experience. Together, these projects have prepared me to design and build distributed storage, index, and query systems that are scalable, fault-tolerant, and easy to manage — and to leverage AI tooling both to accelerate my own engineering workflow and to integrate AI-powered capabilities directly into the products we ship.

Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to backbone infrastructure that users relied on daily. I designed a cloud-agnostic distributed storage, index, and query system in Java and Spring Boot with PostgreSQL and Redis, handling file operations across Google Cloud Storage, S3, and MinIO via expiring signed URLs — giving me direct, hands-on experience architecting fault-tolerant, multi-tiered systems at the language and framework Amazon's teams depend on. I also orchestrated long-running jobs with AWS Step Functions, improving fault-tolerant error recovery across 100K+ weekly executions through structured retry and dead-letter policies, and optimized distributed query performance in PostgreSQL using window functions, materialized views, and indexing to cut reporting latency for business stakeholders. This breadth of experience — from Java and Spring Boot distributed service design to AWS-native orchestration and agile delivery — positions me to contribute meaningfully to the SPACE team's core engineering responsibilities: building the platform that enables multi-channel communication experiences for millions of Selling Partners around the world.

I have always been passionate about customer obsession and the passion for invention that sit at the heart of Amazon's mission to be Earth's most customer-centric company — building products that create real, measurable impact for users who depend on them. The SPACE team's work delivering critical communication at scale to Selling Partners via email, SMS, mobile push, and external API integrations is exactly the kind of high-impact, cross-cutting engineering challenge I want to be part of. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

